SIMPLE: turban
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Turban
<hw>Tur"ban</hw> <pr>(t⟦ucir⟧r"b⟦ait⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>turband</ets>, <ets>turbant</ets>, <ets>tolibant</ets>, F.
<ets>turban</ets>, It. <ets>turbante</ets>, Turk. <ets>tulbend</ets>,
<ets>dulbend</ets>, fr. Per. <ets>dulband</ets>. Cf.
<er>Tulip</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A headdress worn by men in the
Levant and by many Muslims of the male sex, consisting of a cap, and a
sash, scarf, or shawl, usually of cotton or linen, wound about the cap,
and sometimes hanging down the neck.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of headdress worn by women.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The whole set of whorls of a
spiral shell.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turband</ent>⟦br⟧
